<SLUG> BC-BBA-ANGELS-LADN </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
ANGELS SETTLE ON STONEMAN
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By JOE HAAKENSON  
 San Gabriel Valley Tribune  
<TEXT>
<P>
   ANAHEIM _ The Angels will hold a news conference today at noon
to announce they have hired West Covina High graduate Bill Stoneman
as the club's general manager.
</P>
<P>
   Stoneman, who has been a front office executive with the
Montreal Expos since 1983, was expected to be named GM before the
start of the World Series. Angels president Tony Tavares had
decided on Stoneman, but Walt Disney Co. chairman and CEO Michael
Eisner suddenly decided to get involved in the interview process.
</P>
<P>
   Eisner had Bob Watson, Omar Minaya and Jim Duquette come back
for repeat interviews, and the club also called in White Sox
assistant GM Dan Evans for an interview Friday.
</P>
<P>
   But Stoneman ultimately became the club's choice. His experience
with the Expos _ developing quality players despite a significant
lack of funds _ impressed the Angels.
</P>
<P>
   It also signifies a change in Stoneman's career goals. In
previous years, Stoneman had turned down inquiries about his
availability as a GM because he didn't want a job with limited
security while his children were growing up.
</P>
<P>
   ``I really didn't have an interest in being a GM in the past,''
said Stoneman, who graduated from West Covina High in 1962 and also
attended Mt. San Antonio College. ``I never really pursued it. But
I came to a point in my life where now both of our kids are grown
and living on their own. So really it's only the two of us left.''
</P>
<P>
   Stoneman will be expected to get to work immediately, with his
first duty to hire a manager. Don Baylor, who was the top choice of
many in the organization, was hired by the Cubs. Chris Chambliss,
the Yankees hitting coach, is a top candidate.
</P>
<P>
   Stoneman also will have 11 days of exclusive negotiating rights
with pitcher Chuck Finley. After Nov. 11, Finley is free to talk
with all clubs.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
