ethnic differences.''
</P>
<P>
   Rep. Jose Serrano, a Bronx Democrat and the ranking Puerto Rican
member in the House, said: ``There was a time when all you had to
do was get up and say a few Spanish words or eat the right Spanish
food and you were an amigo. Now, the issues are much deeper.''
