<P>
   HEALTH-GENETICS _ First there was the couple who advertised they
would pay $50,000 for an egg from a tall, athletic, college student
with high scores on the Scholastic Aptitude Test.
</P>
<P>
   Then there was the fashion photographer on the Internet who
offered to auction models' eggs to buyers willing to pay up to
$150,000 in hopes of having a beautiful child. (OK, so some
observers now say that was just a ruse to attract visitors to his
pornography site. He did make the offer.)
</P>
<P>
   And that got us to wondering. What if you could pre-select the
specific traits your heart desired?
</P>
<P>
   Want the brains of Stephen Hawking? You got 'em. The body of
Arnold Schwarzenegger? It's yours! The athletic ability of Michael
Jordan? The musical ability of Beethoven or the Beatles? By James
A. Fussell. 835 words.
</P>
