<P>
   AIRCRASH (Undated) _ Ledeall: Investigators locate the EgyptAir
jet's black box, but have yet to retrieve it; new details about the
plane's descent suggest it was intact when it fell from 33,000 feet
to 19,000 feet; the Coast Guard and Navy effort is officially
labeled a recovery effort; teams are working against time in trying
to retrieve the plane, as bad weather is expected Tuesday. By
Robert D. McFadden.
</P>
<P>
   With photos and graphics.
</P>
<P>
   SHEPARD-TRIAL (Denver) _ The judge in the Matthew Shepard trial
ruled Monday that lawyers for a man accused of murdering the gay
college student last year may not use a ``gay panic'' defense. The
judge said their strategy was little more than an attempt to show
that their client suffered temporary insanity or diminished
capacity. Neither defense is recognized by Wyoming law. By Michael
Janofsky.
</P>
<P>
   MUSEUM-SUIT (New York) _ A federal judge ruled Monday that Mayor
Rudolph Giuliani violated the First Amendment when he cut city
funding and began eviction proceedings against the Brooklyn Museum
of Art for mounting an exhibition of contemporary art he deemed
offensive and sacrilegious. The judge ordered the mayor to resume
the city's monthly payments to the museum and end his campaign to
evict the museum and remove its Board of Trustees. By David
Barstow.
</P>
