<P>
   STOCK-FRAUD-VIOLENCE (Undated) _ Until recently, the seedy world
of ``penny stocks'' _ cheap but very risky securities that are
easily manipulated by insiders at the expense of naive public
investors _ had been considered relatively safe, where bribes were
far more likely than bullets. But the killings in New Jersey of two
young stockbrokers last week, although still not definitively
linked to their business life, nevertheless underscored what people
who have studied the industry for years had already concluded:
Violence among people involved in stock fraud is on the rise. By
Diana Henriques.
