r a BC-DIET-EXERCISE-COX     11-01 1480
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-DIET-EXERCISE-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;    
 &HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Losing weight 101: Eat less, move more
 &HT;    By Lillian Lee Kim
 &HT;    c. 1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   ATLANTA _ Count calories. No, count fat grams.
</P>
<P>
   All right, you can have some fat, but only the good kind. Eat
more protein and less sugar. Eat more fiber and less dairy. Eat six
small meals, not three big ones.
</P>
<P>
   Snack. Don't snack. Don't touch pasta. Don't even look at that
Halloween candy.
</P>
<P>
   Exercise 30 minutes, three times a week. Or 10 minutes, three
times a day, three times a week. Or 90 minutes on the days with the
letter A in them.
</P>
<P>
   Every diet and exercise program says: Eat this, do that.
</P>
<P>
   The truth is, losing weight and improving your health boils down
to this: Eat less, move more.
</P>
<P>
   At heart, we know this. Most of America knows this.
</P>
