<HEADER>
A5553 &Cx1f; tdt-z
u a BC-SPOT-BUDGET-BOS &LR;      11-01 0397
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-SPOT-BUDGET-BOS </SLUG>
  
 For Release TUESDAY AMs, November 2, 1999  
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   The Boston Globe plans to move the following stories for use by
NYTimes News Service clients.
</P>
<P>
   &UR;  &LR; For questions about stories, contact  &UR; Frank Perrotta  &LR; at the
Boston Globe,  &UR; 617-929-2597. &LR;  For individual purchase of graphics
or photos please call 212 556-4204 or -1927.
</P>
<P>
   All stories will bear the BOS designator.
</P>
<P>
   &UR;  &LR;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; THE CRASH OF FLIGHT 990 (i) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   CRASH-EGYPTAIR (Newport, R.I.) _ Recovery crews collect human
remains and a large piece of doomed Egyptair Flight 990. Pinging
sounds are heard from one of the plane's ``black boxes.'' By
Matthew Brelis and Thomas Farragher. 1500 words. (i and a coding)
</P>
<P>
   CRASH-FAMILIES (Cairo) _ Families waiting for visas at the US
Embassy are filled with questions and a sense of dread at having to
travel to Rhode Island and wait for naval vessels to search the
murky waters south of Nantucket. 1000 words.
</P>
