buying and home refinancing business of the past 2 years. (Harte,
Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 15. WITH GRAPHIC
</P>
<P>
   BANK-FEES _ There is a backlash brewing against the rising fees
charged by banks to use other banks' ATM machines. A handful of
states and cities, including Iowa, Connecticut and Santa Monica,
Calif., are so sick of the fees, which average about $1.25
nationwide, they've completely banned them. The Pentagon is
considering abolishing ATM fees at military bases. And San
Francisco residents vote on a similar measure Tuesday. The fee ban
is expected to pass easily but court challenges from the banking
industry are assured. (Meadows, Atlanta Journal-Constitution) WITH
GRAPHIC
</P>
