results. The lodging company also warned about a downturn in the
hotel market. (Poole, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   USERY _ ATLANTA _ Bill Usery founded the Center for the
Workplace a few years ago as a way to help companies and people
resolve problems on the job. It's the only center of its kind in
the Southeast. We talk with Usery about how the workplace has
changed. This is a big week for the center, which hosts a two-day
conference on alternative dispute resolution. On Thursday, the
center unveils a computer lab where schools, business and
individuals can come to work out their differences using
technology. (Joyner, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
