   TEACHERS-LAUSD (Los Angeles) -- Citing low pay, overcrowded
classrooms and broken-down schools, leaders of the Los Angeles
teachers' union demanded a 6 percent pay raise and better working
conditions Monday and announced a series of demonstrations designed
to draw attention to their frustrations. By Sherry Joe Crosby.
(Will move on the ``n'' California news wire.)
