<P>
   DISNEY-HONG KONG (Los Angeles) -- Maybe Walt Disney Co. can't
straighten out ABC. Maybe its Disney Stores are getting stale, and
apparently its Club Disney concept wasn't popular enough to expand
nationally as Disney planners once hoped. But when it comes to
Disney's core business _ amusement parks and family movies _ Disney
is still the best in the world. That's why Hong Kong officials are
willing to spend billions of dollars to develop the latest Disney
amusement park, and why Burbank-based Disney will only have to pony
up $300 million. Hong Kong needs Disney to attract tourists its
lost since the island city transfered from British to Chinese
hands. By Dave McNary. (Will move on the ``n'' California news
wire, the ``a'' national wire and ``f'' financial wire.)
