<P>
   AUTO-SALES (Detroit) _ John Smale, the director who led a rare
management coup at General Motors Corp. seven years ago this month,
plans to retire in May, a GM spokesman said Monday. The man Smale
and the GM board installed as chief executive back then, John
Smith, may retire at about the same time, according to board
members and others close to the company. By Robyn Meredith.
</P>
<P>
   (The story is scheduled to move by 9 p.m. ET.)
