<P>
   SCOTLAND-TECH (Glasgow, Scotland) _ Scotland is trying to break
its economic dependence on manufacturing and imported technology by
promoting collaboration between university researchers and
corporate partners. The new push aims at harnessing Scotland's
output of well-qualified college graduates in a high-technology
revolution, which may already be under way in the corridor of
technology companies between Glasgow and Edinburgh known as Silicon
Glen. By Alan Cowell.
</P>
