<P>
   &QL; 
TV-GOODY (Undated) _ Whither Mariah? That was the big controversy
going into the debut Monday of CBS' The Early Show, a fact that
tells you all you need to know about the state of network morning
``news'' shows. By BILL GOODYKOONTZ. Story will move in the ``E''
category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
CURLS (undated) We've noticed - and we've counted - that there are
like a dozen girls with long curls in the spotlight today. From
Felicity's Keri Russell and Providence's Melina Kanakaredes to Ally
McBeal's fab four (Dyan Cannon, Jane Krakowski, Lisa Nicole Carson,
and, this season, sort of, Calista herself), it seems we've come a
long way from the straight days of Marcia Brady. Maybe this is
about the au naturelness of the '90s, maybe this is about the loads
of curl control product on the market today, or maybe this is about
missing the girl with curls on a long-gone loved sitcom: Seinfeld's
Elaine. BY JAIMEE ROSE. &QL; 
 &QL; 
PIMA3(MAYCOBA, Mexico) _ Here in the bosom of the Sierra Madre in
northwestern Mexico, scientists working with the Pima Indians have
found proof that diet and intense exercise offer protection from
diabetes. The Pimas who live here come from the same genetic stock
as the Pimas who live in central Arizona. Yet while the Gila River
community south of Phoenix is being decimated by the ``Pima
Plague,'' diabetes has barely touched this Mexican village. By
GRACIELA SEVILLA. Story will move in the ``A'' category. &QL;
</P>
