Monday. Seeking to stamp out a growing political brush fire that
started here, the AT&AMP;T Corp. argued before a federal appeals court
Monday that the city exceeded its authority last year when it
sought to force AT&AMP;T to open its cable lines to rival Internet
service providers. (John Gress/New York Times Photo)
