<P>
   (NYT22) NEW YORK-- Nov. 1, 1999 -- AIRCRASH-8 11-01 -- Reporters
cover the arrival on Monday of relatives who lost loved-ones on
EgyptAir Flight 990 at JFK Airport. The Cairo-bound EgyptAir Boeing
767 was carrying 217 people when it plunged into the Atlantic from
33,000 feet early Sunday, a half-hour after leaving New York's
Kennedy Airport. The plane went down without a distress call or any
other indication of trouble from the pilots. (Ruby Washington/New
York Times Photo) MAGS OUT
</P>
<P>
   (NYT21) BOSTON -- Nov. 1, 1999 -- BOSTON-CANCER-2, 11-01 -- Jose
Navarro, a 40-year-old Boston flea market vendor, is surprised by
what he learns from reading an anticancer pamphlet. The
quarter-million English-and-Spanish brochures, Boston's largest
public health mailing ever, are the flashiest element of the city's
``crusade against cancer.'' (Jared Leeds/New York Times Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT20) BOSTON -- Nov. 1, 1999 -- BOSTON-CANCER-1, 11-01 --
Esther Ellis, 71, reads an anticancer pamphlet while waiting to
receive a mammogram. Over the last few days, every household in
Boston, in theory, has been mailed a brochure describing how to
prevent cancer and to detect it early if it develops. (Jared
Leeds/New York Times Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT19) STUDENCANE, Yugoslavia -- Nov. 1, 1999 -- KOSOVO-WINTER,
11-01 -- Hanife Gega, an ethnic Albanian, prepares tea in the ruins
of her home last Friday. Her house, like many in the village in
southern Kosovo, was burned with such ferocity by Serb forces that
aid organizations have categorized it as irreparable and fit only
for demolition. Despite the United Nations' promises that every
family in Kosovo will have a dry room for the winter, many
families, the Gegas included, will be camping outside. (Andrew
Testa/New York Times Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT18) ABOARD MERCHANT MARINE TRAINING SHIP KINGS POINTER,
South of Nantucket Island -- Nov. 1, 1999 -- AIRCRASH-7, 11-01 -- A
crewman recovers debris from EgyptAir Flight 990 on Sunday south of
Nantucket Island. The debris was found by crewmen aboard the
Merchant Marine training vessel and handed over to the Coast Guard
later Sunday. (Daniel Robson/New York Times Photo) MAGS OUT
</P>
<P>
   (NYT17) KINGSTON, R.I. -- Nov. 1, 1999 -- AIRCRASH-6, 11-01 --
Government officials examining debris from EgyptAir Flight 990 on
Davisville Pier 2 in Kingston on Monday. Coast Guard search crews
gave up hope Monday of finding anyone alive from the flight, but
found a large piece of wreckage and detected a signal believed to
be from one of the plane's ``black boxes.'' (Chang W. Lee/New York
Times Photo)
