<P>
   ATTENTION EDITORS: The following photos are part of tonight's
New York Times Photo Package, moving Monday, 11/01/99. Photo
clients will automatically receive these photos via AP's
PhotoExpress or may download them from either the Wieck Photo
Database in Dallas at 972-392-0888 or from NYTPhotos on Newscom at
305-448-8411. Non-clients can make individual purchases by calling
(888) 603-1036 or 212-556-4204.
</P>
<P>
   (NYT31) ABOARD MERCHANT MARINE TRAINING SHIP KINGS POINTER,
South of Nantucket Island -- Nov. 1, 1999 -- AIRCRASH-10, 11-01 --
Debris from EgyptAir Flight 990 lies aboard the Merchant Marine
training ship after it was recovered on Sunday from the ocean south
of Nantucket Island. Coast Guard search crews gave up hope on
Monday of finding anyone alive from the doomed flight, but found a
large piece of wreckage and detected a signal believed to be from
one of the plane's ``black boxes.'' (Troy Gosswiller/New York Times
Photo) MAGS OUT
</P>
<P>
   (NYT30) NEW YORK -- Nov. 1, 1999 -- AIRCRASH-9, 11-01 -- Tamer
Omar, brother of a co-pilot in training on Egyptair Flight 990,
Heshema Omar, is surounded by the press as he walks outside the
Ramada inn at John F. Kennedy airport. All over the world, families
and friends sifted through pictures - mental and sentimental ones
as well as photographs - of the passengers and crew members who
died Sunday when Egyptair Flight 990 fell into the Atlantic Ocean
off Nantucket. (Angel Franco/New York Times Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT29) NEW YORK -- Nov. 1, 1999 -- MUSEUM-SUIT, 11-01 -- From
left, Robert Rubin, charman of the board of the Brooklyn Museum of
Art, Arnold Lehman director of the museum and attorney Floyd Abrams
before a news conference on Monday. A federal judge ruled on Monday
that Mayor Rudolph Giuliani of New York violated the First
Amendment when he cut city funding and began eviction proceedings
against the museum for mounting an art exhibition the mayor deemed
offensive and sacrilegious. (Dith Pran/New York Times Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT28) NEW YORK -- Nov. 1, 1999 -- SCI-FITNESS-WATER, 11-01 --
Doctors say too much water during endurance events like a long run
can be dangerous. Though athletes need to drink regularly during a
race to prevent dehydration, experts say that excess water can lead
to hyponatremia, a potentially fatal condition that is rare but
increasing among recreational athletes. (Steve Berman/New York
Times Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT27) NEW YORK -- Nov. 1, 1999 -- LACHAPELLE-FASHION-3, 11-01
-- From left, Barry Diller, Diane Von Furstenberg and Miuccia Prada
showed up to be counted Interview magazine's 30th anniversary party
last Thursday night at the Kit Kat Club. Despite hints of
decadence, hardly any of the usual crew of guests seemed shocked by
the evening's proceedings. (Miles Ladin/New York Times Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT26) NEW YORK -- Nov. 1, 1999 -- LACHAPELLE-FASHION-2, 11-01
-- The theme of the evening was the ``Hotel LaChapelle,'' for the
photographer David LaChapelle's new book. And what's a hotel
without topless bell boys and bell girls? (Miles Ladin/New York
Times Photo) LITE
</P>
<P>
   (NYT25) NEW YORK -- Nov. 1, 1999 -- LACHAPELLE-FASHION-1, 11-01
-- The rapper Lil' Kim performing in a hip hugger (it hugged only
one hip) at Interview magazine's 30th anniversary party last
Thursday night at the Kit Kat Club. Lil' Kim is the real thing, an
invention, a performer whose body and obvious lack of inhibition
make you feel she is totally in control of the stage. (Miles
Ladin/New York Times Photo)
</P>
