Gaining Insight,'' which he calls ``an autobiography of my eyes,''
to be published on Wednesday by Alfred A. Knopf. Grunwald, 76, has
been slowly losing his sight since 1992 because of macular
degeneration (a disease of the central retina, which picks up the
finest details of what people see). It affects 15 million Americans
and is the biggest single cause of legal blindness among the
elderly. (Sara Krulwich/New York Times Photo) LITE
</P>
<P>
   The New York Times News Service
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
